---
const styles = [
  { name: "The Aggregator", desc: "Collector of others' wisdom." },
  { name: "The Apothegist", desc: "Anchors modern practice to classical wisdom." },
  { name: "The Author", desc: "Surfaces best-practices from lived experience." },
  { name: "The Academic", desc: "Builds the case from data and footnotes." },
  { name: "The Actor", desc: "Reports from the trenches of doing the work." },
];
---

<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 px-6 fade-in">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-10 lg:gap-14 items-start">
      <div class="md:col-span-2">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-3">A Tool for Your Authors &middot; Free</p>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl leading-tight mb-4">The Thought Leader Compass</h2>
        <p class="text-navy-soft leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Twenty questions. Five archetypes. The Compass identifies an author's Primary and
          Secondary thought-leadership styles&mdash;and the kind of book they're built to write.
          For publishers, it's a low-friction way to help qualify a prospective author and frame
          the conversation before signing.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://platteclark.com/assessment"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="inline-block text-xs tracking-[0.22em] uppercase font-medium text-gold border-b border-gold pb-1 hover:text-navy hover:border-navy transition-colors"
        >
          platteclark.com / assessment &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="md:col-span-3 bg-navy text-cream p-6 sm:p-8">
        <p class="text-xs tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-gold-soft mb-5">The Five Styles</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          {styles.map((s) => (
            <li class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-3 border-b border-cream/15 pb-3 last:border-b-0 last:pb-0">
              <span class="font-heading text-lg text-cream sm:w-44 flex-shrink-0">{s.name}</span>
              <span class="text-sm text-cream/70 leading-relaxed">{s.desc}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
